ting his own Windwalker Writers' Workshop.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eDan's first published story appeared on Feb. 15, 1982, the day his daughter, Jane Kathryn, was born. He's always attributed that coincidence to \"helping in keeping things in perspective when it comes to the relative importance of writing and life.\"\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eDan has been a full-time writer since 1987 and lives along the Front Range of Colorado—in the same town where he taught for 14 years—with his wife, Karen, his daughter, Jane, (when she's home from Hamilton College) and their Pembroke Welsh Corgi, Fergie. He does much of his writing at Windwalker—their mountain property and cabin at 8,400 feet of altitude at the base of the Continental Divide, just south of Rocky Mountain National Park. An 8-ft.-tall sculpture of the Shrike—a thorned and frightening character from the four Hyperion/Endymion novels—was sculpted by an ex-student and friend, Clee Richeson, and the sculpture now stands guard near the isolated cabin.","isGrAuthor":false,"works":{"__typename":"ContributorWorksConnection","totalCount":222},"profileImageUrl":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/authors/1427999015i/2687._UX200_CR0,12,200,200_.jpg","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/2687.Dan_Simmons","user":null,"viewerIsFollowing":null,"followers":{"__typename":"ContributorFollowersConnection","totalCount":10776}},"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.eX-KKjRR_5nqw4-ECrdlOQ":{"id":"kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.eX-KKjRR_5nqw4-ECrdlOQ","__typename":"Contributor","name":"Gary Ruddell","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3992512.Gary_Ruddell","isGrAuthor":false},"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.VIfTzhX_aUqAkaq2zBg2FQ":{"id":"kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.VIfTzhX_aUqAkaq2zBg2FQ","__typename":"Contributor","name":"Gaetano Luigi Staffilano","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/5182335.Gaetano_Luigi_Staffilano","isGrAuthor":false},